HEADWORD: lovebird
<hw>lovebird</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A small Australian parakeet
(<spn>Melopsittacus undulatus</spn>) usually light green with black and
yellow markings in the wild but bred in many colors; also called the
<altname>budgie</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> budgerigar, budgereegah, budgerygah, budgie, grass
parakeet, shell parakeet, <spn>Melopsittacus undulatus</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>small African parrot noted for showing affection for
their mates.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>loved</ent>⟦br⟧
